would know he wasn't in a gang.

17:29.178 --> 17:33.184
He wrote poetry, collected
books, he was in the jazz band.

17:34.318 --> 17:35.686
Okay. Thank you.

17:37.420 --> 17:38.854
Um, did you get all that?

17:38.856 --> 17:40.588
We appreciate your time.

17:40.590 --> 17:42.758
Will you please send the next person in?

17:44.762 --> 17:46.929
Uh, can I speak with Detective Thompson?

17:47.164 --> 17:49.196
He's not available right now,

17:49.198 --> 17:51.638
but if you remember anything,
you should get in touch with us.

17:52.569 --> 17:59.741
<i>♪ I'll be going home</i>

17:59.743 --> 18:07.316
<i>♪ See the light, see the sun</i>

18:07.318 --> 18:13.691
<i>♪ I'm just going home ♪</i>

18:23.501 --> 18:27.668
<i>I don't suppose any of us
got much sleep last night.</i>

18:27.670 --> 18:30.705
<i>Like most of you probably,</i>

18:30.707 --> 18:32.540
<i>I wept a little,</i>

18:32.542 --> 18:34.541
<i>I prayed a little.</i>

18:34.543 --> 18:37.947
<i>Kevin will be missed by the
teachers for his diligence.</i>

18:38.182 --> 18:40.648
<i>He will be missed by the jazz band,</i>

18:40.650 --> 18:43.251
<i>who is short one
excellent trombone player.</i>

18:43.253 --> 18:45.854
- Trumpet, but it's all brass.
- <i>A dear friend to many of you.</i>

18:45.856 --> 18:48.790
<i>Mostly, he'll be missed
by his loving parents.</i>

18:48.792 --> 18:50.424
I'm sorry.

18:50.426 --> 18:51.893
Sir! I'm really sorry.

18:51.895 --> 18:53.462
I didn't mean to be
disrespectful or interrupt,

18:53.464 --> 18:54.695
but I just had to say something

18:54.697 --> 18:56.798
- that's really important.
- <i>Addison.</i>

18:56.800 --> 18:59.734
I saw Kevin at the coffee shop
yesterday right before it happened.

18:59.736 --> 19:01.536
Actually, Phoebe and I both did.

19:01.538 --> 19:04.505
And then after I heard the
news, I went back to coffee shop,

19:04.507 --> 19:07.709
and one of the news crew guys told me that

19:07.711 --> 19:10.279
they're going to write this
whole thing off as a gang killing.

19:10.281 --> 19:12.780
Which means they probably won't
even go after the guy who did it

19:12.782 --> 19:14.415
because there's such a small chance

19:14.417 --> 19:15.849
of them actually solving the case.

19:15.851 --> 19:17.919
<i>Addison, could you sit down please?</i>

19:17.921 --> 19:20.355
I mean, if anyone here knew Kevin,
they knew he wasn't in a gang.

19:20.357 --> 19:21.822
<i>Addison, please, enough.</i>

19:21.824 --> 19:23.325
I think this is something
we should talk about.

19:23.327 --> 19:25.029
Why am I the only one saying anything?

19:25.262 --> 19:26.728
<i>Addison, please. I've asked
you politely. Sit down!</i>

19:26.730 --> 19:28.763
Does no one care?

19:28.765 --> 19:30.298
<i>I want to hear everything you
have to say, in my office!</i>

19:30.300 --> 19:31.502
All right. Okay.

19:32.936 --> 19:34.636
<i>See me later.</i>

19:39.576 --> 19:41.975
<i>Our emotions are raw.</i>

19:41.977 --> 19:44.311
<i>Everybody in this room is hurting.</i>

19:44.313 --> 19:45.379
Really?

19:45.381 --> 19:46.716
<i>Respect is important.</i>

19:52.555 --> 19:54.621
So what's going on with you?

19:54.623 --> 19:56.390
What do you mean, sir?

19:58.361 --> 20:02.597
Look, there has been a marked
deterioration of your behavior

20:02.599 --> 20:04.335
and your attitude lately.

20:06.503 --> 20:07.605
How are you doing?

20:09.438 --> 20:11.004
I'm fine.

20:12.609 --> 20:15.079
Loss of a parent is a big deal, Addison.

20:16.646 --> 20:19.483
This has nothing to do with my mother, sir.

20:21.584 --> 20:23.417
All right.

20:23.419 --> 20:24.988
Here's what I suggest you do.

20:26.523 --> 20:28.623
Cut the theatrics.

20:28.625 --> 20:31.059
Let the police do their job.

20:31.061 --> 20:32.627
And you work your ass off.

20:32.629 --> 20:34.495
Make your mother proud.

20:34.497 --> 20:36.565
And I'll talk to Chicago.

20:36.567 --> 20:39.103
Tell them what an asset
you are to the school.

20:54.783 --> 20:57.418
<i>- Hey, no cameras in here. Turn it off.
- Sure.</i>

20:57.420 --> 20:59.386
<i>I'm here to see Detective Thompson.</i>

20:59.388 --> 21:00.789
<i>I still see the red light.</i>

21:00.791 --> 21:02.057
<i>Turn it off now.</i>

21:02.059 --> 21:03.459
<i>Sorry. Sorry.</i>

21:03.461 --> 21:04.925
You have an appointment?

21:04.927 --> 21:07.529
Not particularly, but I
need to speak with him.

21:07.531 --> 21:10.398
He's very busy right now.

21:10.400 --> 21:12.769
Okay. I'm going to wait, all right?

21:23.546 --> 21:24.780
Hi, Detective.

21:24.782 --> 21:25.813
So you're the kid with the camera.

21:25.815 --> 21:27.648
Yeah, that's right.

21:27.650 --> 21:29.684
We've got your statement.

21:29.686 --> 21:32.020
I understand that there's
something that you'd like to add.

21:32.022 --> 21:36.691
Yeah. Um, you guys know that Kevin
Broadus was not in a gang, right?

21:36.693 --> 21:38.926
We don't know that.

21:38.928 --> 21:40.895
How do you know that?

21:40.897 --> 21:42.731
Um, well, I mean, I went to...

21:42.733 --> 21:44.699
You know, I've been friends
with him for a while,

21:44.701 --> 21:47.702
and I know that he wasn't in a gang.

21:47.704 --> 21:50.638
Who told you that he was in a gang?

21:50.640 --> 21:53.107
I thought you came here
to tell us something.

21:53.109 --> 21:56.711
I mean, I am here... I just...
I need to know what's going on.

21:56.713 --> 21:58.847
I don't have time for this.
Could you deal with this kid?

21:58.849 --> 22:00.648
- Yeah, I got it.
- Please sir, listen!

22:00.650 --> 22:02.750
My friend just got killed.

22:02.752 --> 22:06.557
And you can't expect me just to sit
around and not do anything about it, okay?

22:09.693 --> 22:13.927
Listen, son. I know he was your friend,

22:13.929 --> 22:17.632
and believe me, we want to catch
whoever did this just as much as you do,

22:17.634 --> 22:21.770
but right now, we're dealing with
24 homicides in this district alone,

22:21.772 --> 22:24.571
and that's just in the past two weeks.

22:24.573 --> 22:26.974
I'm sorry, but if you don't
have anything new to tell us,

22:26.976 --> 22:29.045
I have to get back to work.

22:30.446 --> 22:31.948
Take it easy now.

22:46.596 --> 22:47.631
Hey.

22:55.004 --> 22:57.038
I was looking for you.

22:57.040 --> 22:58.639
You okay?

22:58.641 --> 23:00.143
Yeah, I'm all right.

23:03.179 --> 23:05.515
Do you want to talk about it? Or...

23:07.216 --> 23:09.183
The police have already
made up their minds.

23:09.185 --> 23:10.886
What?

23:10.888 --> 23:12.587
You don't know that.

23:12.589 --> 23:14.088
Listen, Phoebe, one second
we were talking to him,

23:14.090 --> 23:16.656
and the next he's gone. It
just doesn't make any sense.

23:16.658 --> 23:19.961
Everyone is just moving
on like nothing happened.

23:19.963 --> 23:21.128
Addy.

23:21.130 --> 23:22.330
Someone needs to do something.

23:26.570 --> 23:29.240
Addy, I know after what
happened with your mom...

23:30.541 --> 23:32.540
You know, sometimes

23:32.542 --> 23:35.076
bad things, I don't know,
Addy, they just happen.

23:35.078 --> 23:36.245
Phoebe. That's really deep.

23:36.480 --> 23:38.182
I feel so much better. Thank you.

23:39.817 --> 23:43.053
Addison. I'm just trying to help you.

23:49.126 --> 23:51.262
<i>♪ Nowhere to run</i>

23:52.795 --> 23:54.898
<i>♪ The whole world won't find you</i>

23:56.500 --> 23:58.669
<i>♪ Six degrees of</i>

24:00.070 --> 24:02.540
<i>♪ Separation from you</i>

24:03.706 --> 24:05.743
<i>♪ I'm not moving</i>

24:07.076 --> 24:10.110
<i>♪ Till the sun shines on me</i>

24:10.112 --> 24:12.582
<i>♪ Said I've been longing</i>

24:14.117 --> 24:17.985
<i>♪ Longing for apricity</i>

24:17.987 --> 24:19.989
<i>♪ I'm not moving</i>

24:21.256 --> 24:24.959
<i>♪ 'Til the sun shines on me</i>

24:24.961 --> 24:27.298
<i>♪ I've been longing ♪</i>

24:33.704 --> 24:35.069
Addison?

24:35.071 --> 24:36.136
Hi.

24:36.138 --> 24:37.605
Can I help you?

24:37.607 --> 24:38.609
Yeah. Uh...

24:40.077 --> 24:42.079
Mr. Venderleun needs toner.

24:43.913 --> 24:45.015
Again?

24:46.183 --> 24:48.148
You wait here.

24:48.150 --> 24:49.253
Okay.

25:06.569 --> 25:09.171
You tell Mr. Venderleun
from me that these resources

25:09.173 --> 25:11.339
are for the entire school
and not just for his class.

25:11.341 --> 25:13.377
Okay, I will. Thank you so much.

25:20.949 --> 25:22.819
<i>♪ Call out your name</i>

25:24.620 --> 25:26.924
<i>♪ I said I'd find you ♪</i>

25:31.794 --> 25:34.828
Hey! Hey, there's something...
There's something I gotta show you.

25:34.830 --> 25:37.165
I have Mandarin in, like, five minutes.

25:37.167 --> 25:39.767
- Mandarin? No. This is really important.
- Yes. Look, I can't.

25:39.769 --> 25:41.970
I skipped it last time
so I could sleep with you.

25:41.972 --> 25:45.272
- So I have to do it today.
- Come on!

25:45.274 --> 25:47.008
<i>Look. This
is from Mrs. Strauss.</i>

25:47.010 --> 25:49.309
"Kevin has begun to show
signs of emotional trouble.

25:49.311 --> 25:51.279
"The recent slide in
academic results suggest

25:51.281 --> 25:54.715
"he may be dealing with
significant emotional difficulties

25:54.717 --> 25:56.684
"outside of school,

25:56.686 --> 25:59.119
"which he is reluctant to
elaborate upon in our sessions."

25:59.121 --> 26:00.788
Christ, Addison.

26:00.790 --> 26:02.257
What do you think that means?

26:02.259 --> 26:03.426
I don't know.

26:03.660 --> 26:05.694
I think I should talk to Strauss.

26:05.696 --> 26:07.095
And say what?

26:07.097 --> 26:09.129
"Hi, I stole your file,

26:09.131 --> 26:11.199
"and, you know, I would love if
you could talk me through it"?

26:11.201 --> 26:13.734
No, obviously not, but I think
this could lead to something.

26:13.736 --> 26:15.839
What if we could figure this out?

26:20.243 --> 26:22.944
Don't you even care?

26:22.946 --> 26:24.779
That's not what this is about.

26:24.781 --> 26:27.115
Phoebe. Come on. We... Like...

26:27.117 --> 26:29.984
I saw your posters
today outside of the gym.

26:29.986 --> 26:32.086
- I tore them down.
- What? Why?

26:32.088 --> 26:33.988
'Cause, Addison, everyone's
making fun of you.

26:33.990 --> 26:35.990
- They know it's you.
- So you're embarrassed by me?

26:35.992 --> 26:37.157
No, I'm not embarrassed by you.

26:37.159 --> 26:38.826
It's okay to have sex with me,

26:38.828 --> 26:40.860
but you don't want people
to know we're friends?

26:40.862 --> 26:42.731
Of course not! I mean, of course
it's okay that we're friends.

26:42.733 --> 26:43.464
Listen, if you're ashamed
of me, just tell me, okay?

26:43.466 --> 26:45.366
No, you idiot!

26:45.368 --> 26:47.268
I did it because of in spite
of how stupid you're being,

26:47.270 --> 26:49.706
I actually give a shit about you.

26:59.782 --> 27:01.415
Um, can I borrow your
phone? This could be a lead.

27:01.417 --> 27:02.850
Jesus Christ.

27:02.852 --> 27:05.119
Come on! Let me borrow your phone.

27:15.465 --> 27:17.134
- Hello?
<i>- Hello.</i>

27:18.769 --> 27:19.934
Addison?

27:21.038 --> 27:22.039
Addis...

27:23.974 --> 27:27.908
- Who was it?
- I don't know. They hung up.

27:27.910 --> 27:31.913
Addison, you don't seem to realize
that I'm going through this, too.

27:31.915 --> 27:35.282
And I can't stop thinking
about it either, okay? But...

27:37.419 --> 27:39.453
It's not about you.

27:39.455 --> 27:42.859
And there's nothing you
can do to change it, okay?

27:44.494 --> 27:47.097
Now I'm late for class. I gotta go.

28:16.158 --> 28:17.357
<i>Hi, you've
reached the Schacht family,</i>

28:17.359 --> 28:19.493
<i>Sarah, Theo and Addison.</i>

28:19.495 --> 28:21.896
<i>We can't come to
the phone right now.</i>

28:21.898 --> 28:24.538
<i>So leave us a message, and we'll
get back to you as soon as we can.</i>

28:27.003 --> 28:29.937
<i>Uh, hello. This is Principal
Karlstadt at Robert Kennedy High.</i>

28:29.939 --> 28:35.309
<i>I would like, if you can, for you to
come in tomorrow at 8:30 into my office.</i>

28:35.311 --> 28:38.111
<i>It's a matter of some urgency.</i>

28:38.113 --> 28:40.214
Parents and children
should be in touch with each other.

28:40.216 --> 28:41.736
We are in touch with each other.

28:41.784 --> 28:43.317
Through a pager.

28:43.319 --> 28:45.319
Except, he had to use my
daughter's phone to call...

28:45.321 --> 28:47.053
All kids borrow each other's
phone all the time, don't they?

28:47.055 --> 28:49.123
- He doesn't have a cell phone?
- No. Is that a problem?

28:49.125 --> 28:50.565
Why didn't you get him a cell phone?

28:50.792 --> 28:51.992
Okay, let's all calm
down. Let's stay very calm.

28:51.994 --> 28:53.560
It's not a problem. It's a matter of...

28:53.562 --> 28:55.062
- It's a safety issue.
- Could we calm down please?

28:55.064 --> 28:57.063
I'm just trying to make sense of this.

28:57.065 --> 29:00.568
So, his son has put himself

29:00.570 --> 29:02.870
smack dab in the middle of a murder case.

29:02.872 --> 29:04.371
- Am I right?
- Well...

29:04.373 --> 29:06.240
Listen, my son is a good
kid. Can I just say that?

29:06.242 --> 29:07.575
I mean, he's been through
a lot this last year.

29:07.577 --> 29:09.242
Yes.

29:09.244 --> 29:11.311
He's lost his mother and
now he's lost a friend.

29:11.313 --> 29:14.214
What I'm trying to say is that
I think he's just trying to help.

29:14.216 --> 29:17.085
Right. I am not gonna let his kid

29:17.087 --> 29:19.087
jeopardize my daughter's life,

29:19.089 --> 29:20.590
nor her future for that matter.

29:20.822 --> 29:24.191
Okay. I'm gonna stop us right here.

29:24.193 --> 29:28.162
This is a very, very
precarious time for all of us.

29:28.164 --> 29:29.562
So I'd like you to keep that in mind

29:29.564 --> 29:32.299
when you discuss this with your children.

29:32.301 --> 29:34.001
Yes. Of course.

29:34.003 --> 29:36.037
Thank... Thank you for
the meeting, Mr. Karlstadt.

29:36.039 --> 29:39.906
It's been very educational. Thank you.

29:39.908 --> 29:43.210
Okay, I'll speak to you again
after you talk to your children.

29:43.212 --> 29:46.183
Thank you very much. I'll
talk with him tonight.

29:51.920 --> 29:53.921
- Hi, beautiful.
- Hi.

29:53.923 --> 29:55.322
You doing okay?

29:55.324 --> 29:57.325
Yeah. Yeah, I'm good.

29:57.327 --> 29:59.563
Um, so, what's up with
your asshole boyfriend?

30:01.598 --> 30:03.901
It's just that I heard some
weird stuff, that's all.

30:05.068 --> 30:06.267
Do you want to talk about it?

30:06.269 --> 30:08.405
No. Not really.

30:09.238 --> 30:11.540
Oh... Okay.

30:14.276 --> 30:16.511
- Hi.
- Hey.

30:16.513 --> 30:19.146
Uh, could I have a word with you?

30:19.148 --> 30:20.348
Yeah, what's up?

30:20.350 --> 30:22.383
Can I talk to you in private?

30:22.385 --> 30:24.385
Yeah. Sure. Um...

30:24.387 --> 30:27.187
Hey, Alex, will you just watch
my stuff? I'll be right back.

30:27.189 --> 30:28.222
Yeah, sure.

30:28.224 --> 30:29.357
Thanks.

30:29.359 --> 30:31.157
I kind of wanted your advice.

30:31.159 --> 30:32.292
Yeah?

30:32.294 --> 30:33.964
Something to do with Kevin.

30:35.063 --> 30:36.996
Yeah. Um...

30:36.998 --> 30:38.935
I was in the coffee shop when it happened.

30:39.635 --> 30:41.603
- Really?
- Yeah.

30:41.605 --> 30:44.975
I saw something, and I don't
know if I should tell Addison.

30:45.675 --> 30:47.176
Tell him what?

30:48.211 --> 30:49.476
Addison.

30:49.478 --> 30:51.412
Mrs. Strauss. Do you have a minute?

30:51.414 --> 30:52.715
Sure. Come in.

30:52.948 --> 30:55.549
The guy who killed Kevin was white.

30:55.551 --> 30:58.185
I saw his wrist when
he pushed the door open.

30:58.187 --> 31:01.556
I know something was going
on with Kevin before he died.

31:01.558 --> 31:03.523
And I heard that you and him were talking

31:03.525 --> 31:07.161
because he was going through
some emotional difficulties.

31:07.163 --> 31:09.430
So, what do you think it means?

31:09.432 --> 31:11.665
I don't know, but I told the cops,

31:11.667 --> 31:13.466
but I don't think they're
looking in the right place.

31:13.468 --> 31:15.435
Why?

31:15.437 --> 31:17.538
I mean, I heard Kevin was
hanging out with that kid Noel.

31:17.540 --> 31:19.272
- Noel?
- Yeah.

31:19.274 --> 31:22.376
And I know he's mixed up
with some heavy people.

31:22.378 --> 31:23.677
They're dangerous.

31:23.679 --> 31:25.747
What we talked about was confidential.

31:25.982 --> 31:29.549
Just like the conversation we're
having right now is confidential.

31:29.551 --> 31:31.418
Yeah, of course.

31:31.420 --> 31:34.254
But I just want to know
if there's anything,

31:34.256 --> 31:37.090
you know, if you had any idea
of what was going on with him.

31:37.092 --> 31:40.627
Addison, if you want to talk about
how you feel about what's happened,

31:40.629 --> 31:41.763
we can do that.

31:41.997 --> 31:43.598
No, I'm all right. Thank you.

31:43.600 --> 31:47.568
Look, just promise me you won't
tell any of this to Addison.

31:47.570 --> 31:50.169
Just not right now, okay?

31:50.171 --> 31:51.440
Yeah. Okay.

31:52.574 --> 31:54.576
- Thanks, Bo.
- Yeah. I'll see you.

31:54.578 --> 31:55.612
Yeah.

31:57.714 --> 31:59.445
I was at your school today.

31:59.447 --> 32:03.486
And I was catching a lot of shit about you.

32:04.587 --> 32:06.056
About this.

32:08.057 --> 32:09.659
What's up with this, hmm?

32:12.061 --> 32:13.562
What's going on?

32:16.532 --> 32:17.767
Addison?

32:20.535 --> 32:22.238
Remember that day

32:24.240 --> 32:25.606
that Kevin was killed?

32:25.608 --> 32:27.407
Yeah.

32:27.409 --> 32:30.478
I drove back to the coffee
shop after it happened.

32:30.480 --> 32:32.616
That's why I didn't call you.

32:33.250 --> 32:34.482
Okay.

32:34.484 --> 32:36.149
And I...

32:36.151 --> 32:38.752
I saw his body.

32:38.754 --> 32:41.457
Yeah, I saw Kevin. Like,
I saw them wheel him out.

32:43.493 --> 32:45.492
Here's this kid.

32:45.494 --> 32:47.293
He gets murdered,

32:47.295 --> 32:48.797
and no one cares.

32:49.031 --> 32:50.598
That's not true, Addy.
You know that's not true.

32:50.600 --> 32:52.099
No, it is! That's what it seems like.

32:52.101 --> 32:54.236
People care. They do. They just...

32:55.503 --> 32:57.504
Will you just do me a favor?

32:57.506 --> 33:00.406
Just stop this nonsense. This
is... This is crazy, Addison.

33:00.408 --> 33:02.643
It's not nonsense. I'm just
trying to do something good.

33:02.645 --> 33:06.280
Yeah, I... I understand, I think
I do, what you're trying to do.

33:06.282 --> 33:08.683
But this is a murder investigation.

33:08.685 --> 33:10.384
You don't know what could happen.

33:10.386 --> 33:12.153
Nothing's gonna happen!

33:12.155 --> 33:15.125
Well, I couldn't take it if
anything did happen to you.

33:19.396 --> 33:20.761
Just...

33:20.763 --> 33:23.330
If you can't do it for me,

33:23.332 --> 33:24.734
do it for her.

33:25.568 --> 33:27.434
All right?

33:27.436 --> 33:28.571
Yeah.

33:39.682 --> 33:42.416
<i>Video Diary. Day 23.</i>

33:42.418 --> 33:44.284
<i>I don't know, maybe my dad's right.</i>

33:44.286 --> 33:45.566
<i>Maybe I'm not thinking straight.</i>

33:49.559 --> 33:53.394
Maybe I shouldn't forget
about the rest of my life.

33:53.396 --> 33:54.397
Phoebe!

33:56.666 --> 33:57.731
Hey.

33:57.733 --> 33:59.299
What's up?

33:59.301 --> 34:00.302
Hi.

34:03.805 --> 34:04.907
What?

34:07.377 --> 34:14.748
Look. So, I know the other night
was purely a practical thing for you.

34:14.750 --> 34:17.819
And, you know, I have
nothing to compare it to,

34:17.821 --> 34:20.554
except for maybe porn and stuff.

34:20.556 --> 34:22.458
But I just have to say

34:23.793 --> 34:27.194
that it really was sensational,

34:27.196 --> 34:29.697
in the original meaning of the word.

34:29.699 --> 34:32.835
And I have a strong and overwhelming desire

34:33.735 --> 34:35.538
to do it again.

34:40.810 --> 34:42.675
That's bad, huh?

34:42.677 --> 34:44.647
Well, you know,

34:46.616 --> 34:50.451
when I woke up this morning, I...

34:50.453 --> 34:53.790
I looked over at the pillow
where your head had been.

34:54.757 --> 34:55.822
Uh...

34:55.824 --> 34:56.826
And I...

34:58.728 --> 35:01.665
And I kind of wished it was still there.

35:10.739 --> 35:12.773
I don't know, we're probably

35:12.775 --> 35:15.375
- just romanticizing it.
- Romanticizing it. Yeah. That's classic.

35:16.679 --> 35:18.512
But, uh...

35:18.514 --> 35:20.648
Maybe if we did it again...

35:20.650 --> 35:22.918
What? It might break the spell?

35:24.286 --> 35:26.387
That works.

35:26.389 --> 35:28.355
- Should we...
- Yeah.

35:28.357 --> 35:29.458
Okay.

35:32.527 --> 35:34.427
Are you sure your dad's not home?

35:34.429 --> 35:36.262
Oh, yeah, yeah, yeah. I'm sure.

35:36.264 --> 35:38.666
He's out shooting bridges for
a Belgian tourist brochure.

35:38.668 --> 35:40.770
Long way from the
<i>Washington Post, huh?</i>

35:47.409 --> 35:48.511
What?

35:50.346 --> 35:53.848
That... That
was pretty good. Right?

35:53.850 --> 35:55.949
I mean, what do you think?

35:55.951 --> 35:57.686
Better, same?

35:59.422 --> 36:00.557
Worse?

36:02.324 --> 36:04.625
Not worse, but...

36:04.627 --> 36:06.460
Okay.

36:06.462 --> 36:09.032
I mean, the spell is definitely broken.

36:10.565 --> 36:11.567
Yeah.

36:14.536 --> 36:15.705
Really?

36:23.746 --> 36:25.615
No, Addy.

36:28.683 --> 36:30.719
I want you to hold me.

36:45.735 --> 36:47.869
Is it just a one-time
thing? I mean, like...

36:47.871 --> 36:51.505
I mean, if we do do this
again, which I hope we will,

36:51.507 --> 36:56.012
I mean, like, do you want to usually
do the holding afterwards or beforehand?

36:57.813 --> 37:00.082
Usually afterwards, I'm
guessing. That's good.

37:01.484 --> 37:03.384
I'm just curious, you know.

37:03.386 --> 37:05.554
- I want to be...
- Shut up.

37:06.022 --> 37:07.324
Okay.

37:10.292 --> 37:12.360
Okay. Um...

37:12.362 --> 37:14.097
So, what? I guess we just keep...

37:14.330 --> 37:16.896
We keep doing this until
the feeling wears off?

37:16.898 --> 37:19.465
Yeah. Yeah, I'll call you.

37:19.467 --> 37:20.569
Okay.

37:25.842 --> 37:27.840
How are you getting home?

37:27.842 --> 37:30.202
I'm gonna grab a cab. Don't
worry about it. It's fine, okay?

37:35.551 --> 37:36.884
Hi.

37:36.886 --> 37:37.987
Hey.

37:39.788 --> 37:41.121
I brought dinner.

37:41.123 --> 37:43.056
Um, I already ate actually, but thank you.

37:43.058 --> 37:44.523
Okay.

37:44.525 --> 37:45.828
How was your trip?

37:46.828 --> 37:47.930
Good.

37:49.665 --> 37:51.066
How was class?

37:52.400 --> 37:53.733
Fine.

37:53.735 --> 37:57.637
I learned five more ways to say "hello."

37:57.639 --> 38:00.407
It was eventful.

38:00.409 --> 38:02.878
Should we talk about Addison Schacht?

38:03.913 --> 38:05.679
Wow!

38:05.681 --> 38:07.815
- You really have people everywhere, huh?
- Really?

38:07.817 --> 38:09.583
Addison Schacht. Okay.

38:09.585 --> 38:10.951
What?

38:10.953 --> 38:12.820
What's the problem?

38:12.822 --> 38:15.956
We moved up the hill and they moved down.

38:15.958 --> 38:17.657
I went in to your school yesterday,

38:17.659 --> 38:21.163
and I had a meeting with Karlstadt.

38:21.397 --> 38:24.665
He told me about Addison's
so-called "investigation"

38:24.667 --> 38:27.634
into the Broadus murder
and your involvement in it.

38:27.636 --> 38:29.737
I'm not involved in it.

38:29.739 --> 38:31.840
He's a friend of mine. That's it.

38:33.442 --> 38:34.775
So he's just a friend, huh?

38:34.777 --> 38:37.146
What does it matter?

38:37.380 --> 38:39.079
What do you have against him?

38:39.081 --> 38:41.148
It's not his fault that
his life has been so shitty.

38:41.150 --> 38:42.683
His mom died.

38:42.685 --> 38:44.451
I'm not talking about his mother dying.

38:44.453 --> 38:47.822
I'm talking about you pulling
this shit with your friend.

38:47.824 --> 38:50.590
And I just don't want you
to get involved in something

38:50.592 --> 38:53.128
that will most definitely hurt you.

38:56.699 --> 38:59.836
<i>♪ Only memories remain</i>

39:03.906 --> 39:07.509
<i>♪ Only memories remain</i>

39:11.614 --> 39:14.617
<i>♪ For a time There by the sea</i>

39:18.821 --> 39:22.592
<i>♪ There was only you and me</i>

39:26.061 --> 39:29.699
<i>♪ In a land that time forgot</i>

39:32.868 --> 39:37.005
<i>♪ You uttered
sweet forget-me-nots</i>

39:40.777 --> 39:44.581
<i>♪ And you know yeah, I never will</i>

39:47.782 --> 39:51.920
<i>♪ But sometimes
life has other ideas</i>

39:54.956 --> 39:57.056
<i>♪ And though we both know... ♪</i>

39:57.058 --> 40:00.927
<i>Addison Schacht, please
report to the Principal's office.</i>

40:00.929 --> 40:03.532
<i>Addison Schacht to the
Principal's office.</i>

40:06.636 --> 40:08.869
That's it, Addison. Last chance.

40:08.871 --> 40:10.103
What happened?

40:10.105 --> 40:11.038
They're suspending me for a week.

40:11.040 --> 40:13.239
What?

40:13.241 --> 40:15.141
Because they looked in my locker for
posters and they found Kevin's file.

40:15.143 --> 40:17.613
Okay. Well, what are you
going to do about it?

40:19.781 --> 40:22.215
Now I've got nothing to lose.

40:22.217 --> 40:24.016
Addison, they didn't expel you, okay?

40:24.018 --> 40:27.219
Just go home and... And chill out.

40:27.221 --> 40:29.958
They might not put it on your record.

40:32.661 --> 40:34.505
<i>A suspect
was arrested on Thursday</i>

40:34.529 --> 40:36.195
<i>in connection to a separate robbery.</i>

40:36.197 --> 40:37.931
<i>Sunday
morning at 4:30,</i>

40:37.933 --> 40:40.567
<i>violence was unleashed
downtown on a taxi driver.</i>

40:40.569 --> 40:41.902
<i>In other news tonight,</i>

40:41.904 --> 40:43.802
<i>police are still looking for leads</i>

40:43.804 --> 40:46.572
<i>in the case of slain Kennedy High
School student Kevin Broadus,</i>

40:46.574 --> 40:49.175
<i>whose killer fled the scene
on a red Honda motorcycle.</i>

41:22.911 --> 41:24.844
- Hi.
- Hi.

41:24.846 --> 41:27.081
Um, is Addison home?

41:27.083 --> 41:30.753
No. Well, he should be, but no, he's not.

41:31.286 --> 41:32.786
Phoebe?

41:32.788 --> 41:34.020
- Yeah.
- Oh!

41:34.022 --> 41:35.956
- Hi.
- Hi.

41:35.958 --> 41:37.958
Well, why don't you come in? Yeah, yeah.

41:37.960 --> 41:39.159
Come on in.

41:39.161 --> 41:40.630
Yeah, okay. Um...

41:45.167 --> 41:49.737
Don't mind me. It's chili night, and
things tend to get out of control.

41:49.739 --> 41:52.105
Oh, it's fine. Don't worry about it.

41:52.107 --> 41:54.177
So, how are you doing?

41:54.842 --> 41:56.342
Um...

41:56.344 --> 41:59.779
I'm okay. You know, considering everything.

41:59.781 --> 42:00.817
Yeah, I'm sure.

42:01.951 --> 42:04.817
Do you want to sit down? Yeah.

42:04.819 --> 42:07.119
- Sure. I don't mind standing, though, it's...
- Here.

42:07.121 --> 42:09.056
No...

42:09.058 --> 42:11.824
Some of this stuff out of the way here.

42:11.826 --> 42:13.826
Don't mind the mess.

42:13.828 --> 42:15.061
It's okay.

42:15.063 --> 42:16.663
How's your mom?

42:16.665 --> 42:19.368
- You've known her for a while, right?
- Mmm-hmm.

42:19.601 --> 42:23.136
Yeah, since... Well, since
she first came to Washington.

42:23.138 --> 42:25.371
That's almost 20 years now.

42:25.373 --> 42:29.208
Was she always so...

42:29.210 --> 42:32.112
I don't know, like that?

42:32.114 --> 42:34.681
Your mom's a perfectionist.

42:34.683 --> 42:37.150
But she's had to work real
hard to get where she's at,

42:37.152 --> 42:40.289
and you seem to be turning out pretty good.

42:42.824 --> 42:44.991
How do you think Addy's doing?

42:44.993 --> 42:47.694
I don't know actually.

42:47.696 --> 42:49.232
You know, I hope he's okay.

42:56.971 --> 42:58.073
Addy?

43:00.109 --> 43:02.342
- Hey, Dad.
- Hey.

43:02.344 --> 43:04.143
I saved some chili.

43:04.145 --> 43:06.880
Uh, I'm not really hungry.
I'm just gonna go to my room.

43:06.882 --> 43:08.284
Hi, Addy.

43:17.326 --> 43:19.125
What are you doing here?

43:19.127 --> 43:20.393
Oh, we're just having
some ice cream. Want some?

43:20.395 --> 43:21.997
Just waiting on you.

43:23.732 --> 43:25.435
Addison, come on!

43:27.670 --> 43:28.838
Hey!

43:34.208 --> 43:35.444
Addison?

43:36.878 --> 43:38.378
Can I come in?

43:40.415 --> 43:42.882
You have a nice little
chat about me with my dad?

43:42.884 --> 43:45.018
Come on, Addison.

43:45.020 --> 43:47.154
Look, I'm just worried about you.

43:47.156 --> 43:49.355
Well, if you came here to try to
talk me out of doing anything crazy,

43:49.357 --> 43:51.025
- don't bother.
- That's not why I'm here.

43:51.027 --> 43:54.027
I just came back from the police station.

43:54.029 --> 43:57.132
And it was a complete waste of time.

43:59.701 --> 44:00.866
I'm kidding myself.

44:00.868 --> 44:02.469
No one's gonna solve this case,

44:02.471 --> 44:05.174
and there's sure as shit
nothing I can do about it.

44:11.846 --> 44:14.114
All right. I heard something.

44:14.116 --> 44:17.784
And I don't know if it's true or not,

44:17.786 --> 44:20.788
but I've thought about it
and I can't not tell you.

44:20.790 --> 44:22.889
- What?
- You can't overreact, all right?

44:22.891 --> 44:24.424
Because I don't even know
if it means anything yet.

44:24.426 --> 44:25.737
I'm just giving you the information.

44:25.761 --> 44:27.259
Yeah, what is it?

44:27.261 --> 44:28.895
The guy was white.

44:28.897 --> 44:30.329
The guy who killed Kevin.

44:30.331 --> 44:32.935
Bo saw him. He said he was white.

44:34.270 --> 44:36.402
What do you think, it was a race thing?

44:36.404 --> 44:40.007
I don't know. Honestly, I don't think so.

44:40.009 --> 44:43.076
Bo said that Kevin was hanging around
with some pretty dangerous people.

44:43.078 --> 44:44.244
Who?

44:44.246 --> 44:46.048
Do you remember that kid Noel?

44:47.081 --> 44:48.551
Fat Noel from eighth grade?

44:48.784 --> 44:50.951
Yeah. That's who Kevin
was hanging around with.

44:50.953 --> 44:53.119
Phoebe, just because Noel listened
to gangster rap when we were younger

44:53.121 --> 44:54.855
doesn't make him dangerous.

44:54.857 --> 44:56.456
All right, Addison. Well,
look, that's what Bo told me.

44:56.458 --> 44:58.698
He said Kevin was mixed up
with some pretty heavy people.

44:58.793 --> 45:00.092
So there. I told you.

45:00.094 --> 45:02.496
Wait, hold on. Hold on, hold on, hold on.

45:02.498 --> 45:05.398
Um, do you have Noel's number?

45:05.400 --> 45:06.866
Why would I have Noel's number?

45:06.868 --> 45:08.869
I don't... I don't know.

45:08.871 --> 45:11.840
Do you think, um... Do you
think Noel still has a Facebook?

45:14.176 --> 45:17.043
Okay, so it's Tuesday night, around 11:15.

45:17.045 --> 45:19.413
<i>We're on our way to see
our old friend Noel.</i>

45:19.415 --> 45:22.382
<i>Earlier tonight, Phoebe told
me that he might know something</i>

45:22.384 --> 45:24.183
<i>about what happened to Kevin.</i>

45:24.185 --> 45:28.487
<i>So, he invited us to this
address, 267 Otis Street.</i>

45:28.489 --> 45:31.558
Um, this is... This is Otis Street here.

45:31.560 --> 45:33.259
Wait, who are these guys? Maybe this is it.

45:33.261 --> 45:35.128
<i>I don't think this is it.</i>

45:35.130 --> 45:36.862
<i>Oh, no, no, no.
We're good. We're good.</i>

45:36.864 --> 45:38.431
<i>Addison, this
is super sketchy.</i>

45:38.433 --> 45:40.000
<i>If they see that we're,
you know, stressed out,</i>

45:40.002 --> 45:41.201
<i>they're gonna think it's weird.</i>

45:41.203 --> 45:43.003
<i>Just, you know, stay calm.</i>

45:44.272 --> 45:45.538
<i>- Shit! Shit! Shit!
- Go! Go!</i>

45:45.540 --> 45:47.074
<i>Oh, my God!</i>

45:47.076 --> 45:49.043
<i>Why the hell are we down here?</i>

45:49.045 --> 45:50.344
<i>Just give me the
address. What's the address again?</i>

45:50.346 --> 45:51.911
<i>Addison, why are you turning...</i>

45:51.913 --> 45:53.145
<i>No, that's
it. That should be it.</i>

45:53.147 --> 45:54.514
<i>There? That's an alleyway.</i>

45:54.516 --> 45:55.514
Relax, okay? It's gonna be fine.

45:55.516 --> 45:57.116
I'm not gonna relax.

45:57.118 --> 45:58.884
It's gonna be fine. We know him.

45:58.886 --> 46:00.454
- We don't know Noel.
- Yes, we do!

46:00.456 --> 46:02.155
We went to school with him for so long!

46:02.157 --> 46:04.090
- You saw Noel five years ago.
- Five, so what?

46:04.092 --> 46:06.360
- Five years ago.
- Do you see where we are right now?

46:06.362 --> 46:07.994
Fine. You can wait in the car then.

46:07.996 --> 46:10.099
No way. I'm not doing that.

46:15.103 --> 46:17.404
Is this really
where Noel's friend lives?

46:17.406 --> 46:19.105
What's his name again?

46:19.107 --> 46:21.041
He said to ask
for some guy named D. Cash.

46:26.982 --> 46:28.351
Yo, you got visitors.

46:31.453 --> 46:33.520
Come on in.

46:33.522 --> 46:37.226
Take your hands out your pockets,
man. You're making me nervous.

46:39.994 --> 46:41.494
- So, you're Addison.
- Yeah.

46:41.496 --> 46:43.232
- I'm D.
- Hey, man. Good to meet you.

46:47.869 --> 46:49.503
What's your name, baby? Who is this?

46:49.505 --> 46:51.570
You brought me a little gift right here?

46:51.572 --> 46:53.373
I'm Phoebe.

46:53.375 --> 46:55.375
- Phoebe.
- Yeah.

46:55.377 --> 46:57.476
- You want to have some fun?
- I'm okay.

46:57.478 --> 46:58.480
She's with me, man.

46:59.947 --> 47:01.215
Mmm?

47:01.217 --> 47:03.550
- I'm okay.
- What'd you say?

47:03.552 --> 47:06.152
She's... She's with me.

47:06.154 --> 47:08.487
Man, I will slap your
nose off your face, man.

47:08.489 --> 47:10.123
Shut up, Addison.

47:10.125 --> 47:12.391
Yeah, you heard her.
You better shut up, dude.

47:12.393 --> 47:13.395
All right.

47:14.563 --> 47:16.032
Hey, your friend's here.

47:18.500 --> 47:20.967
Noel, wake up, man.

47:20.969 --> 47:24.070
Hey, get your ass up,
Noel. They're here. Wake up.

47:25.273 --> 47:26.308
Is that Noel?

47:27.208 --> 47:29.208
Who's this bitch?

47:29.210 --> 47:30.947
Hey man, it's Addison.

47:32.514 --> 47:36.118
Addison, yeah. Good to see you, man.

47:38.453 --> 47:40.454
You look like shit.

47:40.456 --> 47:42.158
Well, sit down, man.

47:46.494 --> 47:48.661
Uh, so, how you been, man?

47:48.663 --> 47:51.663
You high already man. I'll
take this. Put that shit down.

47:51.665 --> 47:53.166
It's crazy, right?

47:53.168 --> 47:55.337
It's been, like, five years, six years.

47:57.105 --> 47:59.505
Why are you so interested all of a sudden?

47:59.507 --> 48:01.442
Well, um, the reason why I'm here

48:01.444 --> 48:04.277
is because I wanted to
ask you about something.

48:04.279 --> 48:07.079
- Okay. Uh...
- Uh...

48:07.081 --> 48:10.616
The shooting in Northwest at Seven Stars.

48:10.618 --> 48:14.022
I don't know if you know or
not, but this kid Kevin Broadus,

48:15.690 --> 48:18.659
who we know, he was the one who got killed.

48:18.661 --> 48:21.594
Yeah, what are you asking me for?

48:21.596 --> 48:26.334
Well, I... I heard, you know,
you guys were hanging out.

48:27.603 --> 48:30.304
So, what do you think happened?

48:30.306 --> 48:33.172
I mean, we just heard that
the guy who did it was white...

48:33.174 --> 48:35.175
Enough of this shit, man.

48:35.177 --> 48:36.745
Enough.

48:36.978 --> 48:38.746
Noel, you got this kid's number?

48:39.014 --> 48:40.145
No.

48:40.147 --> 48:41.749
I have a pager.

48:41.984 --> 48:43.451
You got a pager.

48:45.054 --> 48:46.386
Where you live, son?

48:46.388 --> 48:48.255
Uh, we're actually from Philadelphia.

48:48.257 --> 48:50.355
We're just visiting.

48:50.357 --> 48:52.358
I know where he lives. You're still
at the same place, right, Addy?

48:52.360 --> 48:54.360
Yeah. Same place.

48:54.362 --> 48:55.972
Good. I think you kids better
get going, man. Get out of here.

48:55.996 --> 48:57.197
No problem.

48:57.199 --> 48:59.331
If we hear something, who knows?

48:59.333 --> 49:01.201
Maybe we'll give you a call.

49:01.203 --> 49:02.402
All right, white boy?

49:02.404 --> 49:05.337
Okay. Thank you. I'll send him my number.

49:05.339 --> 49:08.509
Get your ass home, man.

49:08.511 --> 49:11.078
<i>Why the hell would
you tell them where you live?</i>

49:11.080 --> 49:12.813
Noel still thinks we live in Chevy Chase.

49:13.047 --> 49:15.382
We used to be rich, remember?

49:15.384 --> 49:17.152
Well, that's just great.

49:20.188 --> 49:21.790
Phoebe. I'm really sorry.

49:22.022 --> 49:23.523
- I don't want to hear it from you.
- Okay? I... I am.

49:23.525 --> 49:25.293
- I don't want to hear it!
- Okay.

49:30.766 --> 49:32.401
I need a break.

49:33.502 --> 49:35.503
I can't keep doing this.

49:37.406 --> 49:39.739
I can't be a part of this anymore.

50:24.219 --> 50:25.688
Yeah, hello. Who is this?

50:26.755 --> 50:28.855
Oh, yeah. Yes. This is he.

50:28.857 --> 50:30.190
Yeah, no.

50:30.192 --> 50:32.161
Thank you, sir, for calling.

50:33.795 --> 50:34.830
Yes.

50:36.598 --> 50:38.599
Okay.

50:38.601 --> 50:41.268
Okay. I'll see you then.

50:41.270 --> 50:43.436
Phoebe! Hi. I'm in here.

50:43.438 --> 50:46.306
Listen, I'm hanging up, all right?
Call me if you start to panic.

50:46.308 --> 50:47.309
Bye.

50:48.643 --> 50:49.875
- Good morning.
- Hey.

50:49.877 --> 50:51.578
Can we talk for a minute?

50:51.580 --> 50:53.579
We can talk later. I gotta go.

50:53.581 --> 50:55.551
It'll only take a minute.

50:57.453 --> 50:58.717
Okay.

50:58.719 --> 51:00.353
Well,

51:00.355 --> 51:02.725
Addison Schacht's father
called me last night.

51:04.759 --> 51:05.894
Yeah?

51:06.127 --> 51:09.429
It was kind of illuminating.

51:09.431 --> 51:11.697
I have to admit. I didn't...

51:11.699 --> 51:13.599
I hated the fact that he knows

51:13.601 --> 51:16.471
more about what my own
daughter is doing than I do.

51:17.471 --> 51:19.507
